Implementation details for TD.2 - Structured Logging:

## Architecture Decisions
- Uses Go 1.21+ stdlib log/slog (no external dependencies)
- Options pattern for flexible configuration
- Global logger with convenience functions
- Component-based tagging for filtering

## Logging Package API
- Initialize(opts...Option) - setup global logger
- WithLevel/WithFormat/WithOutput/WithSource - options
- Debug/Info/Warn/Error - convenience functions
- WithComponent(name) - returns tagged logger
- Attr helpers: DeploymentID, InfraID, PlanID, Region, Cost, Err

## CLI Flags Added
- -log-level: debug|info|warn|error (default: info)
- -log-format: text|json (default: text)

## Output Formats
- text: time=2024-01-01T00:00:00Z level=INFO msg="..." key=value
- json: {"time":"...","level":"INFO","msg":"...","key":"value"}

## Why slog?
- Standard library (no dependencies)
- Structured by design
- Handler pattern for customization
- Level-based filtering built in
- Machine-parseable output

## Migration Notes
- Replaced log.Printf with slog.Info/Debug/etc
- Replaced log.Fatal with slog.Error + os.Exit(1)
- Other files still use standard log (can migrate incrementally)

## Testing Strategy
- Test both text and JSON output formats
- Test level filtering
- Test component tagging
- Test attribute helpers
